column1: Field type: Management, either field trial site or organic
Country of origin: Country where sampled field was located
Area: Nearest town/village or region within the country
Field of origin: Field within trial site (block-field, Figure S1) or name of organic field
Established: Year of establishment for field trial or clover/grass pasture
Soil chemical properties include: pH (Rt), Phosphorous, Kalium, Magnesium, Cupper
Soil physical properties include: Humus, Coarse sand, Fine sand, Silt, Clay
Strain from Cavassim et al.. 2020: Name of isolate from pink white-clover nodules isolated from the same field
Genospecies: Genospecies (Kumar et al., 2020) designation of strains isolated from the field

Cavassim, M.I.A., Moeskjær, S., Moslemi, C., Fields, B., Bachmann, A., Vilhjálmsson, B.J., Schierup, M.H., Young, J.P.W. & Andersen, S.U. (2020) Symbiosis genes show a unique pattern of introgression and selection within a rhizobium leguminosarum species complex. Microbial Genomics.

Kumar, N., Lad, G., Giuntini, E., Kaye, M.E., Udomwong, P., Jannah Shamsani, N., Peter W Young, J. & Bailly, X. (2015) Bacterial genospecies that are not ecologically coherent: Population genomics of rhizobium leguminosarum 140133. Open Biology, 5.
